@node Intro "What is X-Traktor?"

Description of X-Traktor:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

      X-Traktor is a GUI for use with LZX, LHA, LZH, ZOO, ZIP, DMS,
      ARJ, RAR and UUcoded archives. It allows you to unarchive,
      create new archives, test and view archives easily and quickly,
      by simply clicking on various buttons.

@endnode

@node Install "Installing X-Traktor"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~

      Installing X-Traktor is easy, simply click on the Install Icon,
      then select where you would like X-Traktor to be installed.
      Note: A Drawer called X-Traktor will be created there for you.
    
      If you prefer a DIY installation, then :

      * Copy IconX into your C: directory (you should already have it,
        but some of the older versions wont work with X-Traktor)
      * Copy the X-Traktor and Guide icons wherever you want to use it.     

@endnode

@node Req "X-Traktor Requirements"

Requirements:
~~~~~~~~~~~~

      * Workbench 3.X
      * Requester.library (should already have it.)
      * LZX       \
      * LHA        \ 
      * ZOO         |
      * UNZIP       | - All needed in C: directory, 
      * DMS         | - for X-Traktor to work fully.
      * UNARJ       |
      * UNRAR       |
      * UUENCODE   /
      * UUDECODE  /
      * UNLZX         (Not necessary but allows faster extraction.)

      Older versions of the above have not been tested with X-Traktor but
      the following versions were used in the development of X-Traktor:

      LZX 1.20 (68020/68030 Version)
      LhA 1.38
      Zoo 2.1
      UnZip 5.1
      DMS Pro 2.20 TURBO
      UnARJ 2.41 (68020 Version)
      UnRAR 2.01 (68020 Version)
      UnLZX 1.25 (68000/68010 Version)
      UUencode/UUdecode v36.6

      * All the above are available from Public Domain or Aminet.
        Aminet UK:  src.doc.ic.ac.uk/aminet/util/arc

      Note: Although X-Traktor is intended for use with hard drives,
            a hard drive is not necessary, but much much faster :)

@endnode

@node Unarc "UnArchiving with X-Traktor"

UnArchiving
~~~~~~~~~~~

      You can UnArchive the following archive types:
      LZX, LHA, DMS, LZH, ZOO, ZIP, ARJ and RAR.

      To unarchive an archive, simply click on the 'UnArc' button.
     
      * Select the file to unarchive.
      * Select a destination path.
      * Thats it, just wait and the archive will be extracted for you.

      Note: With DMS you must enter the destination device to unpack to.
            If an invalid device is given (eg. RAM:) then the default of
            DF0: will be used. Valid entries are DFx: and RAD: etc..

@endnode

@node Arc "Archiving with X-Traktor"

Archiving
~~~~~~~~~

      To create a new archive, click on the 'Arc' button.

      * A new menu appears, now click on the archiving method you want
             
            LZX - Newer, Faster and more Efficient Archiver than LHA.
            LHA - Older Archiver, still used on Aminet.
            DMS - Used for packing entire DOS/NDOS disks.
       UUENCODE - For coding files to send via email.

      * If you select LZX or LHA, then a menu appears which asks you
        what you would like to archive. Select either:
          Directory - to archive the entire contents of a directory.
          Select    - to select specific files to archive.
      * Select a destination path for the new archive.
      * Enter the name of the new archive at the prompt.
      * Thats it, the new archive will be created for you.

      To Select more than one file, hold down the shift key.

      Note: With DMS you must enter the destination device to pack. If
            an invalid device is given (eg. RAM:) then the default of
            DF0: will be used. Valid entries are DFx: and RAD: etc..

      Also: There is no option to create ZOO archives. This is because
            I didnt see any point, since its old and slow.

@endnode

@node CleanUp "CleanUp function"

CleanUp
~~~~~~~
         This function allows you to quickly access the unarchived file
      contents, and delete what you dont want. Archives usually contain
      many files that some users dont require, such as the FILE_ID.DIZ or
      source files.

         To delete the un-required file(s), simply click on the file you
      want to delete or hold down the shift key for multiple files, then
      click on the Delete button.
      
@endnode

@node Test "Testing with X-Traktor"

Testing
~~~~~~~

      You can Test the contents of the following archive types:
      LZX, LHA, DMS, LZH, ZOO, ZIP, ARJ and RAR.

      To test an archive contents, click on the 'Other' button, then
      click on the 'Test' button.

      * Select the archive you want to test.
      * Thats it, the archive will be tested for you.

      If you click on the '<< Back' button then you go back to the
      main menu.

@endnode

@node View "Viewing with X-Traktor"

Viewing
~~~~~~~

      You can View the contents of the following archive types:
      LZX, LHA, DMS, LZH, ZOO, ZIP, ARJ and RAR.

      To view the contents of an archive, click on the 'Other' button,
      then click on the 'View' button.

      * Select the archive you want to view.
      * Thats it, the archive contents will be listed for you.

      If you click on the '<< back' button then you go back to the
      main menu.

@endnode

@node UUdecode "UUdecoding with X-Traktor"

UUdecoding
~~~~~~~~~~

      To UUdecode a document, click on the 'Other' button, then click
      on the 'UUdecode' button.

      * Select the file to UUdecode.
      * Select a destination path.
      * Thats it, just wait and the file will be UUdecoded for you.

      Click on the '<< back' button to go back to the main menu.

@endnode

