@node Bugs "Known Bugs"

Known Bugs
~~~~~~~~~~
      When using selective archiving with LZX you may find that while
      creating the archive the process is suddenly halted, and an
      error message occurs like:

      ***LZX: Cannot open 'Work:St
      ' for input

      Also when using selective archiving with LHA you may find instead
      of the archive being created you get the error message:

      error: Quoted string not terminated!

Why this happens
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      These error messages occur because X-Traktor uses the LZX and LHA
      archivers as there not supposed to be used.
      Selective archiving allows you to select certain files to archive,
      and these files names are held in a string.

      This string is then fed into the LZX and LHA command lines, but LZX
      and LHA have a maximum input string buffer of only 128 characters.
      So if this string is longer than 128 characters then the above error
      messages will occur.

      Note: if the input string is longer than 128 characters then LHA
      wont even attempt to create an archive, but LZX does, even though
      it will fail :)

Solution
~~~~~~~~
      The easiest way to get around this problem is to add only one maybe
      two files at a time to the archive when using selective archiving.
      If you create more archives with the same name, then the files will
      be added to the existing archive with that name.
      The other solution is not to use selective archiving, and only use
      the directory archiving method.      

@endnode

